{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-04-12T16:22+0000", "md5": "CE162D3AF92A947AFA3610C9917447EB", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 4}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 5, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "ACTA 2.0 1 proposes several new functionalities compared to the previous version. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00022339820861816406}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0038365721702575684}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 4}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "ACTA 2.0 provides the following functionalities, visualized in Figure 1: Search on Pubmed.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.016824722290039e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.6033649444580078e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 4}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "ACTA 2.0 Public API.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9988685846328735}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001704692840576172}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 4}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "ACTA 2.0 allows for the automatic extraction and interactive visualization of the arguments contained in the abstracts of clinical trial articles on PubMed, and the automatic analysis of the effects on the outcomes concerning the extracted PICO elements.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.660554885864258e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0022320151329040527}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SciBERT", "normalizedForm": "SciBERT", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "The SciBERT [Beltagy et al., 2019] uncased base model with pretrained weights is used for the sentence representations, finetuned with a learning rate of 2e-5, batch size of 8, maximum sentence length of 256 sub-words tokens per input example during 3 epoch. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8562371730804443}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.7285346984863281e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998557567596436}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010725855827331543}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 34}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "Finally, a refactoring of the ACTA architecture allows now for a modular solution, such that, through a REST API, the different ACTA 2.0 modules are made available to be integrated by external systems.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.732080459594727e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.037040114402770996}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.00011736154556274414}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 34}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "To the best of our knowledge, ACTA 2.0 is the only automated tool which allows for a deep analysis of clinical text from the argumentative point of view to support evidencebased medicine.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.1278858184814453e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.5578881502151489}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.172325134277344e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 34}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "As in the previous version of ACTA, this API is integrated as a search bar to enter queries in the common PubMed format, similarly to the original PubMed web interface.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00022482872009277344}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008227229118347168}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.001099228858947754}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 34}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "As one of the major upgrades, ACTA 2.0 implements a new module to analyse the reported effects an intervention has on the outcomes (O of PICO) in the clinical trial abstract.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.301568984985352e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.3612402081489563}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7881393432617188e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 38}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "We presented a new version of the ACTA system for the argumentative analysis of clinical trial.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.860494613647461e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 37, "offsetEnd": 41}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0", "offsetStart": 42, "offsetEnd": 45}, "context": "In contrast to the previous version, ACTA 2.0 integrates a completely overhauled relation classification module, implementing the methods described by Mayer et al. [Mayer et al., 2021]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.812810897827148e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0034400224685668945}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "EVI-DENCEMINER", "normalizedForm": "EVI-DENCEMINER", "offsetStart": 39, "offsetEnd": 73}, "context": "Few systems tackle similar tasks, like EVI-DENCEMINER [Wang et al., 2020] (which, given a natural language query, automatically retrieves sentence-level textual evidence from a corpora of biomedical literature), RobotReviewer [Marshall et al., 2016;Marshall et al., 2017] (which summarizes the key information of a clinical trial, including the interventions, trial participants and risk of bias), and Ex-aCT [Kiritchenko et al., 2010] (which extracts information containing PICO elements based on a SVM). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021767616271972656}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013287067413330078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7285346984863281e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021767616271972656}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013287067413330078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7285346984863281e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 43, "offsetEnd": 47}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "In this paper, we present a new version of ACTA [Mayer et al., 2019], a web tool designed to assist clinicians in analyzing clinical trials, empowering them with the ability to retrieve the main arguments (i.e., the claims and evidence together with their relations of support or attack) contained in the text.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.244680404663086e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998531341552734}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.8775463104248047e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22, "offsetStart": 746, "offsetEnd": 766}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 70, "offsetEnd": 74}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "Given the importance of this search engine in the health-care domain, ACTA 2.0 maintains the possibility to search for a (set of) abstract(s) directly on the PubMed catalogue, through their API 4 .", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002714395523071289}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003628730773925781}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0016737580299377441}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 84, "offsetEnd": 88}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "For the PICO detection, we rely on the same module employed in the first version of ACTA.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9642288684844971}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0018485784530639648}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7881393432617188e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SciBERT", "normalizedForm": "SciBERT", "offsetStart": 86, "offsetEnd": 93}, "context": "The same pre-trained transformer model types as for relation classification (based on SciBERT combined to a bidirectional GRU and a final CRF) are used to predict one among the fives effect classes in Table 1. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998557567596436}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.4007091522216797e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.7881393432617188e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998557567596436}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010725855827331543}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "SciBERT", "normalizedForm": "SciBERT", "offsetStart": 96, "offsetEnd": 103}, "context": "We use a pre-trained bidirectional transformer language model trained on scientific data, i.e., SciBERT uncased, fine-tuning it for three epochs with the same hyper-parameters we used in the argument component detection module. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9568421244621277}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010725855827331543}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998557567596436}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010725855827331543}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.980232238769531e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WordPiece", "normalizedForm": "WordPiece", "offsetStart": 103, "offsetEnd": 129}, "context": "The dataset splits are the same than in [Mayer et al., 2021] without sentences containing less than 10 WordPiece [Wu et al., 2016]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9806544184684753}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3113021850585938e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9806544184684753}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3113021850585938e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 142, "offsetEnd": 146}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "For the argumentative analysis and the PICO element detection, we replicate the same setting of Mayer et al. [Mayer et al., 2019], evaluating ACTA 2.0 on the same sample of the AbstRCT dataset6 (i.e., 500 abstracts of randomized controlled trials on neoplasm treatment annotated with claim, premise and their relations).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.2159347534179688e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 144, "offsetEnd": 148}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "After the query is executed, when the results are shown, the user can then select one or more abstracts to proceed with the analyses offered by ACTA 2.0.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.019388020038604736}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.029273986816406e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "RobotReviewer", "normalizedForm": "RobotReviewer", "offsetStart": 212, "offsetEnd": 271}, "context": "Few systems tackle similar tasks, like EVI-DENCEMINER [Wang et al., 2020] (which, given a natural language query, automatically retrieves sentence-level textual evidence from a corpora of biomedical literature), RobotReviewer [Marshall et al., 2016;Marshall et al., 2017] (which summarizes the key information of a clinical trial, including the interventions, trial participants and risk of bias), and Ex-aCT [Kiritchenko et al., 2010] (which extracts information containing PICO elements based on a SVM). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021773576736450195}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013287067413330078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021773576736450195}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013287067413330078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ACTA", "normalizedForm": "ACTA", "offsetStart": 348, "offsetEnd": 352}, "version": {"rawForm": "2.0", "normalizedForm": "2.0"}, "context": "Concerning the identification of PICO elements in text, different approaches are proposed in the literature [Dhrangadhariya et al., 2021;Jin and Szolovits, 2018;Trenta et al., 2015] to identify them in text, but none of these approaches tackles the issue of analysing the effects of an intervention on the outcomes of a clinical trial study, as in ACTA 2.0.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008915066719055176}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.002560138702392578}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999243021011353}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999096989631653}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.002272307872772217}}, "references": [{"label": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "normalizedForm": "[Mayer et al., 2019]", "refKey": 22}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Ex-aCT", "normalizedForm": "Ex-aCT", "offsetStart": 402, "offsetEnd": 435}, "context": "Few systems tackle similar tasks, like EVI-DENCEMINER [Wang et al., 2020] (which, given a natural language query, automatically retrieves sentence-level textual evidence from a corpora of biomedical literature), RobotReviewer [Marshall et al., 2016;Marshall et al., 2017] (which summarizes the key information of a clinical trial, including the interventions, trial participants and risk of bias), and Ex-aCT [Kiritchenko et al., 2010] (which extracts information containing PICO elements based on a SVM). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021773576736450195}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013287067413330078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021773576736450195}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0013287067413330078}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.6689300537109375e-06}}}], "references": [{"refKey": 22, "tei": "<biblStruct xml:id=\"b22\">\n\t<analytic>\n\t\t<title level=\"a\" type=\"main\">ACTA A Tool for Argumentative Clinical Trial Analysis</title>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">Tobias</forename><surname>Mayer</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">Elena</forename><surname>Cabrio</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n\t\t<author>\n\t\t\t<persName><forename type=\"first\">Serena</forename><surname>Villata</surname></persName>\n\t\t</author>\n